{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\system\\execution-protocol.md", "content": "500: \n501: ### Adding a New Skill to the Registry\n502: \n503: When creating a new skill (via `engineering-skills` or manually), add a row to this table:\n504: 1. Skill name (kebab-case, matches SKILL.md folder name)\n505: 2. Artifact type (descriptive plural noun)\n506: 3. Example count string\n507: \n508: Also update the skill's session-end block with the matching artifact type one-liner.\n509: \n510: ---\n511: \n512: ## 5. FIC Context Monitoring + Recovery Checkpoint\n513: \n514: Monitor context utilization throughout execution.\n515: \n516: **On hitting 60% context threshold:**\n517: 1. IMMEDIATELY write current output state to disk (even if incomplete)\n518: 2. Mark incomplete sections: `status: pending — context compaction triggered`\n519: 3. Update `_progress.json`: `{ \"status\": \"COMPACTION_NEEDED\" }`\n520: 4. WRITE Recovery Checkpoint (see format below)\n521: 5. LOG: `\"FIC ALERT: Context at {N}% — partial state written for session recovery\"`\n522: \n523: **Recovery Checkpoint** — write to `{progress_folder_path}/RECOVERY-CHECKPOINT-{session_id}.md`:\n524: \n525: ```\n526: (a) Current phase + current file being worked on\n527: (b) Files COMPLETED in this session (paths only — do NOT re-read them)\n528: (c) Key patterns/decisions from plan and research (compact summary, max 30 lines)\n529: (d) Output file contract: path to _progress.json + expected output parameters\n530: (e) Next action to take when resuming\n531: ```\n532: \n533: Note: IMPL-STATE tracks status metadata. Recovery Checkpoint tracks WORKING CONTEXT —\n534: what was in memory when compaction hit. They serve different purposes.\n535: \n536: **After context continuation (compaction boundary), FIRST actions:**\n537: 1. READ Recovery Checkpoint\n538: 2. READ IMPL-STATE\n539: 3. Resume from the \"next action\" in the checkpoint\n540: 4. Do NOT re-read source files already marked COMPLETED in IMPL-STATE files_touched\n541: 5. Re-read ONLY the current file being worked on + plan/research sections for remaining work\n542: \n543: ---\n544: \n545: ## 6. Dual-Format Input Detection\n546: \n547: All skills support two input formats. Detection is automatic.\n548: \n549: | Format | Signal | Handling |\n550: |--------|--------|---------|\n551: | Agent-native | Single `*-SPEC-*.md` in input folder | Parse structured sections directly |\n552: | Legacy | Multiple numbered files (00-XX) in input folder | Read index (00-*), then load files on demand |\n553: \n554: Agent-native is preferred. Legacy is for backward compatibility.\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## 7. REPAIR Mode\n559: \n560: Triggered when `failure_feedback` parameter is provided.\n561: \n562: ### 7.1 FIRST ACTION — Mandatory Reviewer-Comment Absorption\n563: \n564: Before any spec write in REPAIR mode, the agent MUST:\n565: \n566: ```\n567: 1. Read the latest state.json for the current capability/session.\n568: 2. Extract every navigation_history[] entry where action == \"failed_step\"\n569:    AND step matches the current step being repaired.\n570: 3. Concatenate the `reason` text of those entries in timestamp order.\n571:    This is the AUTHORITATIVE reviewer-comment payload — it overrides any\n572:    abbreviated version that may have been passed via the failure_feedback\n573:    parameter alone.\n574: 4. Scan that text for INLINE FILE REFERENCES of the form:\n575:      - \"Line {N} (near: …)\"           — line-anchored content correction\n576:      - \"File: {path}\"                  — file-anchored content correction\n577:      - \"comments file …: {path}\"       — separate comment store\n578:    If a separate comment store path is mentioned, load that file and treat\n579:    its contents as additional ground-truth corrections.\n580: 5. Quote every reviewer instruction verbatim in the agent's internal\n581:    reasoning before proposing any regeneration. Do NOT paraphrase reviewer\n582:    text in the spec — copy the resolution faithfully.\n583: ```\n584: \n585: Skipping any of steps 1-5 is a protocol violation. The reviewer-comment payload\n586: loaded here feeds into Section 7.2 (the directive parser).\n587: \n588: ### 7.2 Directive Application\n589: \n590: ```\n591: 1. Load existing output spec — do NOT start from scratch.\n592: 2. If SESSION_ID needed: extract from existing spec filename.\n593: 3. Parse the reviewer-comment payload from §7.1 into directives:\n594:    { section: \"section_name\" | \"global\", instruction, reason }\n595: 4. FOR EACH section in spec:\n596:    - Has directive → load from existing spec, apply change, rewrite section\n597:    - No directive → preserve existing content verbatim. Do NOT touch it.\n598: 5. \"global\" directive → re-execute full generation (Steps 3 onward)\n599: 6. Re-run all validation checks after fixes.", "metadata": {"start_line": 500, "end_line": 599, "returned_lines": 100, "has_more": true, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": false}}}
