ironment setup fails:\n\n1. Capture the exact error message\n2. Identify the failing command\n3. Report to user with:\n   - What failed\n   - Why it failed\n   - How to fix it (installation instructions, missing dependencies, etc.)\n4. DO NOT proceed to validation if setup failed\n\n## Platform-Specific Considerations\n\n- Activation scripts: Use appropriate syntax (`source` for Unix, `Scripts\\` for Windows)\n- Path separators: Use forward slashes on Unix, backslashes on Windows\n- Shell compatibility: Assume bash/zsh on Unix, PowerShell on Windows\n- Package managers: Verify availability (apt for Ubuntu, brew for macOS, chocolatey for Windows)\n\n## Remember: for running the previous skill instructions\n- NEVER run interactive commands - always use non-interactive flags\n\nUse the previous instructions for executing the user scripts following the rules and guidelines provided.\n"}}
