{"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "C:\\QAx\\002\\context-pack\\project-overview.md", "content": "1: # Project Overview\n2: # Star Wars Lego — Greenfield\n3: \n4: **Document Version:** 1.0\n5: \n6: ## 1. Project Summary\n7: \n8: The Star Wars Lego project is a single-page application (SPA) designed as an educational web application for teaching JavaScript ES6+ and Vue.js 2.x concepts to beginner students. The project focuses on practical programming demonstrations through an interactive Star Wars Lego themed interface.\n9: \n10: ## 2. Project Type\n11: \n12: **Project Type:** Greenfield Development\n13: **Target Domain:** Educational Technology\n14: **Primary Audience:** Beginner JavaScript students, web development learners, programming educators\n15: \n16: ## 3. Core Objectives\n17: \n18: - Demonstrate practical application of JavaScript ES6+ concepts (functions, objects, arrays, loops)\n19: - Teach Vue.js 2.x reactive development patterns\n20: - Provide hands-on DOM manipulation experience\n21: - Create an engaging, interactive learning environment\n22: \n23: ## 4. Technical Stack\n24: \n25: ### Frontend Technologies\n26: - **HTML5:** Semantic markup structure\n27: - **CSS3:** Grid-based layouts, responsive design\n28: - **JavaScript ES6+:** Core programming logic\n29: - **Vue.js 2.x:** Reactive framework for data-binding and components\n30: - **Google Fonts:** Acme and Handlee typography\n31: - **Material Symbols:** Icon system\n32: \n33: ### Architecture Pattern\n34: - **Pattern:** Single Page Application (SPA)\n35: - **Approach:** Simplified MVC with local state management\n36: - **State Management:** Component-level state with Vue.js reactivity\n37: \n38: ## 5. Key Features\n39: \n40: ### Character Gallery\n41: - Grid-based display of 8 classic Star Wars Lego characters\n42: - Interactive hover effects and modern visual transitions\n43: - Character information and interaction capabilities\n44: \n45: ### Search System\n46: - Real-time filtering by character name\n47: - Input validation with required field enforcement\n48: - Dynamic content updates based on search criteria\n49: \n50: ### Social Interactions\n51: - Like/favorite functionality for characters\n52: - Delete/remove characters from the display\n53: - Visual feedback through user-friendly alerts\n54: \n55: ### Personalization\n56: - Customizable greeting messages\n57: - Dynamic title updates based on user interactions\n58: - Personalized user experience elements\n59: \n60: ## 6. Design Specifications\n61: \n62: ### Visual Theme\n63: - **Design Concept:** Space/Star Wars aesthetic\n64: - **Color Palette:**\n65:   - Background: Dark space theme (#111) with galaxy imagery\n66:   - Text: Light gray (#CCC) for readability\n67:   - Highlights: Star Wars yellow (#FD4) for emphasis\n68:   - Alerts: Red (#FF4444) for user notifications\n69: \n70: ### Layout Requirements\n71: - **Container:** Fixed-width, centered layout\n72: - **Minimum Width:** 820px (desktop and tablet focus)\n73: - **Responsive Design:** Adaptive layouts for supported viewports\n74: \n75: ## 7. Technical Constraints\n76: \n77: ### Browser Compatibility\n78: - **Target Browsers:** Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (modern versions)\n79: - **Viewport Support:** Desktop and tablets (820px+ width)\n80: - **No Mobile Support:** Resolutions below 820px not supported\n81: \n82: ### Performance Requirements\n83: - **Loading Priority:** Fast initial load with optimized resources\n84: - **Image Optimization:** Web-ready formats for character images\n85: - **Font Loading:** External Google Fonts (internet connection required)\n86: \n87: ### Dependencies\n88: - **Runtime:** Only Google Fonts require internet connectivity\n89: - **Local Resources:** All other assets hosted locally\n90: - **No Backend:** Pure client-side application\n91: \n92: ## 8. Project Assets\n93: \n94: ### Image Resources\n95: - **Location:** C:\\QAx\\images\n96: - **Content:** Star Wars Lego character images\n97: - **Format:** Web-optimized image formats\n98: - **Usage:** Character gallery and interactive elements\n99: \n100: ## 9. Development Timeline\n101: \n102: ### Current Status\n103: - **Phase:** Ready for development\n104: - **Specification:** Complete (PRD001 v1.0)\n105: - **Code Structure:** Planned for modularity and maintainability\n106: \n107: ### Future Enhancements\n108: - Additional character expansion\n109: - Backend/database integration\n110: - User authentication systems\n111: - Enhanced social features\n112: \n113: ## 10. Quality Requirements\n114: \n115: ### Educational Standards\n116: - Clear code documentation for learning purposes\n117: - Demonstrable programming concepts\n118: - Progressive difficulty for skill building\n119: - Interactive feedback mechanisms\n120: \n121: ### Code Quality\n122: - Modular, maintainable structure\n123: - Component-based architecture\n124: - Performance optimization\n125: - Cross-browser compatibility\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: *Star Wars Lego Project Overview — Globant Delivery Team*", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 129, "returned_lines": 129, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": true, "truncated": false}}}
